<h3>Admission checklist</h3>

<ul class="list-group">
	<li class="list-group-item">Nonrefundable Application fee $40.</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">High School/ Bachelors/ Masters Degree transcript/Diploma/Certificate. The office of Admissions will accept: Photocopies of Original Academic documents (Notarized).
Note: All transcripts and related academic documents issued in language other than English must be accompanied by a certified English translation.</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">TOEFL or IELTS Test Result TOEFL Test 500 (paper based), 173 (computer - based), or 61 (internet - based) and 5.0 (IELTS).</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">Copy of International Passport ID page.</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">Financial Affidavit of Support Form (signed by the student or his/her sponsor).</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">Current Bank Statement (not older than 6 months) showing a Minimum Balance of:
		<ul class="list-group">
			<li class="list-group-item">AA - $13,200</li>
			<li class="list-group-item">BS - $13,200</li>
			<li class="list-group-item">MS - $13,650</li>
			<li class="list-group-item">Post MS - $15,750</li>
			<li class="list-group-item">Dependents - $5,000(Spouse) & $3,500(Per Child)</li>
		</ul>
	
	</li>
</ul>


<h3>Transfer Students</h3>

<p>Please note that you will be required to provide the following documents listed below in addition to the admission requirements.</p>
<ul class="list-group">
	<li class="list-group-item">Copy of F-1 Student Visa and I-94 form</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">Copy of initial I-20 Form used to enter the united states (Stamped by Immigration Office)</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">Copy of current I-20</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">Official Transcripts from your current Univeristy</li>
</ul>


<div class = "page-header">
    <h2>DOMESTIC STUDENTS</h2>
</div>

<h3>Admission checklist</h3>

<ul class="list-group">
	<li class="list-group-item">Nonrefundable Application fee $40.</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">Undergraduate Transcript</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">Undergraduate Certificate</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">A copy of Identification document (driver license, ID card, copy of green card for residents)</li>
</ul>
	
<h3>Transfer Students</h3>
<p>Students transferring to ACCT from another institution must also provide:</p>
<ul class="list-group">
	<li class="list-group-item">Graduate Transcript (If already started classes in another college and may want us to transfer some credits from the previous college.)</li>
</ul>

<p>Applicants whose first language is not English must provide proof of language proficiency by at least one of the following:</p>
<ul class="list-group">
	<li class="list-group-item">TOEFL test score of 550(paper-based), 213 (computer based) or 60 (internet based) and 6.0 (IELTS)</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">Satisfactory completion of a college level post secondary education program or higher in which the language of instruction was English</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">Completion of English as a Second Language (ESL) course(s) taken at an English speaking postsecondary institution</li>
</ul>


	
